# AutoWash Pro — Core Agent Rules

Full context: `AGENTS.md`. Read `docs/BE_INTEGRATION_NOTES.md` before any API/auth work.

## Non-Negotiables

- Backend calls via `@/lib/api` (Axios), never raw `fetch` to BE
- Types/enums from `@/lib/types` — not `lib/data.ts` (legacy mocks only)
- UI copy in **Vietnamese**; mono font for plates, booking IDs, times
- Do not edit `components/ui/*` for feature styling — compose/wrap instead
- Minimal scope: no drive-by refactors; no commit unless user asks
- After login: `tokenStorage.setAccess()` + `tokenStorage.setRole()` for middleware cookies

## BE Auth Reality

- Login: `POST /auth/signin` with `{ email, password }`
- Register: `POST /auth/signup`; OTP verify returns success only → user signs in again
- Refresh: `POST /auth/renew-token` via httpOnly cookie (handled in `lib/api/client.ts`)

## Design

- Primary `#1470af`, cards `rounded-2xl border shadow-sm`, buttons `rounded-xl`
- Reuse: `PortalShell`, `PageHeader`, `EmptyState`, `StatusBadge`, `ConfirmDialog`

## Before Implementing

1. Find similar existing page in same portal
2. Check `docs/TASKS.md` for screen ID (C/M/W/A-xx)
3. Verify API shape in Swagger or existing `lib/api/*.ts`
